<p>

<it>Exclusion</it> showcases the <happening wordnetid="107283608" confidence="0.8">
<event wordnetid="100029378" confidence="0.8">
<psychological_feature wordnetid="100023100" confidence="0.8">
<incident wordnetid="107307477" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../995/19309995.xml">
Komagata Maru</link></incident>
</psychological_feature>
</event>
</happening>
 incident, an incident where Canada turned away 397 Indian dissidents (most of whom were <ethnic_group wordnetid="107967382" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../405/29405.xml">
Sikh</link></ethnic_group>
) as a part of a policy to keep Canada racially white. The Indians on the boat saw this as proof that they were not equal citizens of the British empire, and after being forced to leave Canada and return to Calcutta in India, decided that they would march on the capital in protest of the events that had taken place. </p>
