Amitabh Bachchan has been unfortunately dropped from the  film . The reason being that the Big B does not hold a Canadian passport! Deepa sent a mail to the superstar saying that she could not work with him because the Canadian Government, which is funding half the project, wants the lead actor to have a Canadian passport. Deepa is upset with this stringent rule as it was her dream to work with Amitabh Bachchan. But for her it was $12 million on one side and Big B on the other. And, she decided to have the funds for the film and drop the actor. </p>
<p>

Akshay Kumar is being offered the role of Gurdit Singh</p>
<p>

Akshay Kumar says, "I am not used to working with Oscar Nominated
Directors so it is a great privilege to work with Deepa Mehta. The subject of
this film has moved me, as it is a true representation and a testimony to
human struggles for freedom, justice and equality. I want to portray this real
life tragedy to the world identifying how injustice was done to innocent
people. It is an honour for me to play one of the bravest Sikhs, Gurdit Singh,
in this tragic forgotten moment in history. I salute those brave souls who
sacrificed their lives for justice and equality today."</p>

